    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-04-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 6, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: With reference to your communication
                            of the 2d instant, recommending to consideration the request of the
                            passengers of the captured British steamer Peterhoff to be allowed to
                            leave the vessel with their personal effects, in order to have free
                            access to her Majesty’s consul at New York, and to my reply, I now have
                            the honor to enclose to you the copy of a letter of the 4th of this
                            month from the Secretary of the Navy on the subject.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, your lordship’s obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
